{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","data":{"alias":"dated-circular-velvetworm","description":"## Context\nThe authenticated-authorship merge-gate (`verify-identity`) is live but ADVISORY: `identity.require_authenticated=false` and the store holds 0 signed events. To make the gate actually enforce, write-signing must be rolled out first.\n\n## Success Criteria\n- [ ] Configure self-identity + `identity.signing_key` on the write paths so new events are signed.\n- [ ] Confirm new events verify (`rebar verify-identity` shows `verified` for post-boundary events).\n- [ ] Flip `identity.require_authenticated=true` in the SAME change that enables signing (historical events already grandfathered by `identity.enforce_since`).\n- [ ] Depends on the perf fix (1cc0) so the enforcing gate is fast enough for CI.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Write-signing enabled and producing signed events.\n- [ ] `identity.require_authenticated` flipped on with the grandfather boundary intact.\n- [ ] `verify-identity` enforces on new unsigned/forged events and passes on signed ones.","id":"a422-a27e-44e4-4697","parent_id":"","priority":2,"status":"idea","tags":[],"ticket_type":"epic","title":"Roll out authenticated write-signing + flip identity.require_authenticated to enforce"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783980039061312001,"uuid":"2f414af6-155d-4ff5-8d9c-f28fa6229348"}